item.title: CVE-2018-5539|2024-08-05T05:40:50.516Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20%28asm%29
item.description: Under certain conditions, on F5 BIG-IP ASM 13.0.0-13.1.0.7, 12.1.0-12.1.3.5, 11.6.0-11.6.3.1, 11.5.1-11.5.6, or 11.2.1, when processing CSRF protections, the BIG-IP ASM bd process may restart and produce a core file.

item.title: CVE-2018-5526|2024-08-05T05:40:50.555Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20%28asm%29
item.description: Under certain conditions, on F5 BIG-IP ASM 13.1.0-13.1.0.5, Behavioral DOS (BADOS) protection may fail during an attack.

item.title: CVE-2018-5541|2024-08-05T05:40:50.481Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20%28asm%29
item.description: When F5 BIG-IP ASM 13.0.0-13.1.0.1, 12.1.0-12.1.3.5, 11.6.0-11.6.3.1, or 11.5.1-11.5.6 is processing HTTP requests, an unusually large number of parameters can cause excessive CPU usage in the BIG-IP ASM bd process.
